// Pragmatic mix — share business + screens that are 'design-system' driven,
// but keep platform-defining flows (paywall, onboarding) native.

// shared/commonMain — feed screen, settings, list/detail UI
// shared/androidMain — Activity glue, Hilt entry points
// shared/iosMain — UIViewController wrappers
//
// iosApp/  (native iOS Xcode project)
//   Onboarding screens — pure SwiftUI
//   Paywall — pure SwiftUI (subscription chrome must match Apple guidelines)
//   Tab host — SwiftUI TabView, embeds Shared.MainViewControllerKt.MainViewController() for the rest
//
// androidApp/
//   Main Activity — Compose; embeds shared App() composable directly

// Decision rule: ask whether each screen could ship as 'design system look' or 'native look'.
// Design-system → CMP. Native-look → SwiftUI / Jetpack Compose with shared ViewModels.

